 regimes assess how a group's politics align with their own ideological projects.Explaining, for example, why governments often use extreme repression against weak groups even while working with or tolerating more powerful armed actors, Ordering Violence provides a comprehensive overview of South Asia's complex armed politics, embedded within an analytical framework that can also speak broadly beyond the subcontinent.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aConflict managementzSouth AsiavCase studies. 0aConflict management. 0aInsurgencyxGovernment policy. 0aNon-state actors (International relations) 0aNon-state actors (International relations). 0aPolitical violencezSouth AsiavCase studies. 0aPolitical violence. 4aAsian Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSecurity Studies. 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh  aInsurgency in South Asia, Governments and armed groups, political violence in south asia, insurgency and counterinsurgency.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150176113340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501761133423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501761133/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-07540